===The Riemann tensor===
Directional derivatives are often used in introductory derivations of the Riemann curvature tensor. Consider a curved rectangle with an infinitesimal vector formula_26 along one edge and formula_27 along the other. We translate a covector formula_28 along formula_26 then formula_27 and then subtract the translation along formula_27 and then formula_26. Instead of building the directional derivative using partial derivatives, we use the covariant derivative. The translation operator for formula_26 is thus
formula_34
and for formula_27,
formula_36
The difference between the two paths is then
formula_37
It can be argued that the noncommutativity of the covariant derivatives measures the curvature of the manifold:
formula_38
where formula_39 is the Riemann curvature tensor and the sign depends on the sign convention of the author.

