== Normal derivative ==

A normal derivative is a directional derivative taken in the direction normal (that is, orthogonal) to some surface in space, or more generally along a normal vector field orthogonal to some hypersurface. See for example Neumann boundary condition. If the normal direction is denoted by formula_51, then the normal derivative of a function &quot;f&quot; is sometimes denoted as formula_52. In other notations,
formula_53

== In the continuum mechanics of solids ==

Several important results in continuum mechanics require the derivatives of vectors with respect to vectors and of tensors with respect to vectors and tensors. The directional directive provides a systematic way of finding these derivatives.

